					"patching_rect" : [ 8.0, 121.0, 621.0, 66.0 ],
					"text" : "When a new sample is loaded, it is played through the pfft~, and the resulting phase & amplitude analysis is recorded into a buffer~ inside. The patch then allows resynthesis by scrubbing with \"s pvocFrame\". \"Dither\" adds noise to the frame message and gives the scrub control a continuous sound that might resemble granular synthesis. Multiple instances are OK, either as a bpatcher or not.",
